
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use [set-value] in conjunction with [strings.replace]. It changes the value of the [.result] node by replacing occurrences of the string [[speech]] within its current value with the string "true". The [set-value] slot is used to assign the modified string back to the [.result] node.
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[speech]]
      .:true
